@startuml
title QueryEngine Turn - SDK Shell Wrapping The Inner Loop

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam TitleFontSize 19
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam NoteFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  ArrowColor #5E5A53
  StartColor #8C2721
  EndColor #161616
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

[*] --> Accept

state "Accept\nsubmitMessage(...)" as Accept #E8DDD0
state "Normalize\ntext + attachments" as Normalize
state "Assemble turn context\nsystem / user / tool" as Assemble
state "Inner query loop" as Inner #EFE6D8
state "Consume stream\nevents -> SDK" as Consume
state "Persist\ntranscript + replay markers" as Persist
state "Update session\nmutableMessages etc." as Update #E8DDD0

Accept --> Normalize
Normalize --> Assemble
Assemble --> Inner : invoke query(...)
Inner --> Consume : streamed events
Consume --> Persist
Persist --> Update
Update --> [*]

note right of Inner
  QueryEngine does not run
  the turn itself. It brackets
  one invocation of the inner
  loop and owns everything
  outside that loop.
end note

note right of Update
  Session state survives
  between turns; the inner
  loop is re-entered with it
  pre-populated.
end note

@enduml
